### Sound Null Safety

Dart 3.0 enforces sound null safety. Variables cannot contain `null` unless explicitly declared as nullable.

```dart
void main() {
  String nonNullable = 'Hello'; // Cannot be null
  String? nullable = null;      // Can be null

  // nonNullable = null; // COMPILE ERROR
  nullable = 'World'; // OK
}
```

### Nullable Types

Add `?` after a type to make it nullable.

| Type | Can be null? |
|------|-------------|
| `String` | No |
| `String?` | Yes |
| `int` | No |
| `int?` | Yes |
| `List<String>` | No |
| `List<String>?` | Yes |

### Null Assertion (!)

Use `!` to assert that a nullable value is non-null. Throws at runtime if null.

```dart
void main() {
  String? name = 'Alice';
  String nonNull = name!; // Assert not null
  print(nonNull);
}
```

### Null-aware Operators

| Operator | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `?.` | Safe access | `name?.length` |
| `??` | Default value | `name ?? 'Guest'` |
| `??=` | Assign if null | `name ??= 'Guest'` |
| `!` | Null assertion | `name!` |

### Late Variables

`late` defers initialization. Throw if accessed before assignment.

```dart
class Database {
  late final String connection;

  void init() {
    connection = 'Connected';
  }

  void query() {
    print(connection); // OK if init() was called
  }
}
```

### Type Promotion

```dart
void main() {
  String? name = 'Alice';

  if (name != null) {
    // name is promoted to non-nullable String
    print(name.length); // No need for !
  }

  // Or use early return
  void printLength(String? text) {
    if (text == null) return;
    print(text.length); // Promoted to non-nullable
  }
}
```

> **Key Point:** Null safety is sound in Dart - if the type says non-nullable, you will never get null at runtime. Use `?.` for safe access and `??` for defaults.

codeExample:
class User {
  String name;
  String? email;
  int? age;

  User(this.name, {this.email, this.age});

  String get displayName {
    if (email != null && age != null) {
      return '$name ($email, ${age} years)';
    }
    return name;
  }

  String get emailOrDefault => email ?? 'No email provided';
}

void main() {
  var user = User('Alice', email: 'alice@example.com', age: 30);
  print(user.displayName);
  print(user.emailOrDefault);

  var guest = User('Bob');
  print(guest.emailOrDefault);
}
